parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake line can cause a sudden and complete loss of brake function, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Sudden loss of brake pressure
inability to slow or stop the vehicle
corrosion on the rear brake line.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the right rear caliper can cause excessive wear on the inside of the rotor, leading to a loss of brake function and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Excessive wear on the inside of the rotor
caliper rebuild kits leaking
need for frequent replacement of brake components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause vibration when braking, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Vibration when braking
warped brake rotors
need for frequent replacement of brake components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the ABS can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: ABS activating during normal braking
taking too long to re-engage brakes
feeling of sliding on ice even when there is no ice on the road.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal Chattering and Kicking Back
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The chattering and kicking back of the brake pedal can cause the driver to lose control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Brake pedal chattering and kicking back
feeling of brakes releasing and vehicle continuing to move forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability to steer and brake at the same time can cause the driver to lose control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Inability to steer and brake at the same time
truck pulling hard to the left when brakes are applied
difficulty turning when brakes are applied hard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake controller module can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Brake controller module failure
malfunctioning brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the brake pedal being too close to the accelerator can cause the driver's foot to get stuck under the pedal, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Driver's foot getting stuck under the brake pedal
difficulty braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected failure of the tire can lead to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Tread separation
tire blowout
vibration
unresponsive steering
and loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking and bulging of the sidewall can lead to tire failure, loss of control, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sidewall cracking
bulging
and irregularities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Uneven tire wear can lead to reduced traction, loss of control, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Uneven tire wear patterns
cupping
and vibration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The short valve stem can make it difficult for drivers to check tire pressure, leading to underinflated tires, reduced traction, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Difficulty checking tire pressure due to short valve stem.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque converter can cause the vehicle to become loud and rattle, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle is louder with a rattling noise
the torque converter fails to engage properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the axle seal can cause axle oil to leak onto the brake pads, making it difficult to control the vehicle during hard braking, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Axle oil leaks onto the brake pads
the vehicle is difficult to control during hard braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The drivetrain issues can cause the vehicle to become difficult to control, especially on rough roads, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The drivetrain bangs back and forth
the vehicle is difficult to control
especially on rough roads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driveshaft can cause the vehicle to become undrivable, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The driveshaft comes loose
the vehicle is undrivable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking brake can cause the vehicle to move when parked, especially on steep terrain, which can lead to accidents or loss of life.
symptoms: The parking brake fails to engage
the vehicle moves when parked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to become difficult to control, especially when shifting gears, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The transmission fails to engage properly
the vehicle is difficult to control when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine knock can cause the engine to fail, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine has an internal knock
especially during cold start-up and transmission shifts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the spark plug can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or fires. The loose spark plug can also blow out, causing fuel-air mixture to escape, which can ignite and cause a fire.
symptoms: Spark plug blows out
engine stalls or loses power
loud exhaust noise
gasoline fumes inside the passenger compartment
engine hesitation during acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling or Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling or loss of power can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic. The loss of power can also lead to loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Engine stalls or loses power
hesitation during acceleration
loss of power steering and power brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause oil to leak onto the engine and transmission housing, leading to environmental hazards and waste of precious oil supplies. The fumes coming into the cab can also create a health hazard.
symptoms: Oil leaking onto the engine and transmission housing
fumes coming into the cab
blown head gasket.
